day_2.description:
Breakfast and drive to Lake Nakuru with Picnic lunch in Nairobi. Proceed on driving to the Rift Valley arriving at Lake Nakuru National Park. Late afternoon game viewing & bird watching. Dinner and overnight at Lake Nakuru Flamingo Resort & Spa or similar. Distance: Approx. 410 kms – 6 hrs drive
Meal plan: {Breakfast, Lunch, Dinner}

Lake Nakuru is a shallow soda lake, renowned for its huge concentration of flamingos. It is also a Rhino sanctuary. You embark on a game drive which includes a walk on the shores of the lake to view flamingoes from close range. Keep your eyes open for the elusive Leopard or the Tree climbing lions of this park. The afternoon game drive is included and you will return to your lodge as the sun sets!
